body:
Hi,

is it possible to take a backup of the erigon data directory once fully synced to use as a restore point?

I tried to do the following but seems to not have worked so im unsure if this is possible or if i have done it wrong.


Steps:

**1)  tar or zip the entire erigon directory
2)  move tar or zip file to new host and unzip to excact same dir location
3)  install erigon and ensure .conf file is pointing to the same data dir using:  --datadir=/data/erigon/datadir
4)  start erigon and rpcdeamon
5)  check erigon log which shows the following**


```
tail -f /var/log/supervisor/erigon.err.log
[INFO] [01-05|09:27:34.733] [2/15 BlockHashes] DONE                  in=3m17.750795042s
